es": ["Use Gate 19 as a source for needs, approach and mutual support.", "Use Gate 19 in management_and_environment when discussing support boundaries, available resources and team conditions.", "Use Gate 19 in risks_and_distortions when discussing overgiving, blurred boundaries, anxious guessing or need to be needed.", "Use Gate 19 in communication_and_influence when discussing how to clarify needs, requests and support agreements.", "Use Gate 19 in work_style when discussing how support conditions influence work stability.", "Use Gate 19 in development_potential when discussing clearer requests, boundaries and mutuality."], "forbidden_uses": ["Do not say the candidate is needy because of Gate 19.", "Do not say the candidate is empathic, kind or caring because of Gate 19 alone.", "Do not say the candidate is naturally social or community-oriented because of Gate 19 alone.", "Do not say the candidate is good at resource management, finances or operations because of Gate 19 alone.", "Do not treat Gate 19 as Gate 49 or full Channel 19-49.", "Do not make role-fit, fit_score, vacancy-fit or hiring recommendations from Gate 19."], "preferred_layers": ["management_and_environment", "risks_and_distortions", "communication_and_influence", "work_style", "development_potential", "pro_foundation"], "source_priority": "supporting", "priority_note": "Gate/19 usually supports conclusions about support needs, mutuality, request clarity, approach thresholds and boundaries in management/environment contexts. It may become primary in a layer only when Gate 19 is strongly activated, repeated, connected to Channel 19-49, or central through planet/activation role in support or team conditions context.", "can_be_primary_when": ["full channel/19-49 is present", "gate/19 is activated by a central planet or important activation role in management or support context", "the layer specifically analyses support needs, boundaries, mutuality or team conditions", "several other elements repeat the same theme of needs, support gaps or mutual agreements"], "ai_must_check": ["Is Gate 49 present?", "Is Channel 19-49 defined?", "Which activation carries Gate 19?", "Which line, planet and side are involved?", "How does this interact with type, strategy and authority?", "Does the work environment allow clear support requests?", "Are boundaries of responsibility explicit?", "Are there real work facts showing healthy support or distorted overgiving?"]}, "source_chip": {"base_label": "Настройка взаимной поддержки", "pro_label": "Ворота 19 · Потребности", "short_role": "Добавляет тему потребностей, подхода и взаимной поддержки: где нужен ресурс, внимание, ясный запрос или более бережная договорённость.", "role_in_this_layer": "В слое управления и среды помогает объяснить, почему человеку важны ясные границы поддержки, прямые запросы и понятная взаимность.", "link_target": "element://gate/19"}}'::jsonb,
  '{"primary_context": ["root_center_context", "tribal_ego_circuit_context", "harmonic_gate/49", "potential_channel/19-49", "full_channel_presence_or_absence", "activation_context"], "secondary_context": ["type", "strategy", "authority", "profile", "line_context", "planet_context", "side_context", "emotional_center_context", "work_environment", "role_expectations", "team_support_norms"], "depends_on": "Gate 19 must be read through the whole chart context, especially whether Gate 49 is present and whether Channel 19-49 is defined. It should not be interpreted as generic sensitivity, dependency, empathy, sociality, resource management or emotional principles in isolation.", "related_element_kinds": ["gate", "channel", "center", "activation", "type", "strategy", "authority", "profile"], "context_note": "Gate 19 shows the theme of needs, approach and mutual support. Its final HR expression depends on Root Center context, Tribal Ego Circuit context, harmonic Gate 49, full channel presence, activations, line, planet, side, type, strategy, authority and real work behavior."}'::jsonb,
  '{"base": "Искажённое проявление этой темы — когда внимание к потребностям превращается в тревожное угадывание, спасательство, желание быть нужным или перегруз чужими запросами.", "pro": "Not-Self проявление может возникать, когда pressure of Gate 19 проживается через страх нехватки поддержки, обусловленность tribal expectations, размытые границы, неподходящую среду или попытку заслужить принятие через постоянную помощь.", "warning_signals": ["человек берёт на себя больше поддержки, чем может выдержать", "помощь оказывается без ясного запроса", "человек обижается, если его вклад не замечают", "появляется тревога, если он не чувствует себя нужным", "потребности не называются прямо", "отказ воспринимается как отвержение", "границы помощи становятся размытыми", "поддержка превращается в скрытую обязанность"], "recovery_conditions": ["ясные запросы", "проговорённые границы поддержки", "право на отказ", "понятная зона ответственности", "доступ к реальным ресурсам", "культура прямого обсуждения потребностей", "разделение помощи и спасательства", "уважение к взаимности"]}'::jsonb,
